Section 1:
SR 5 Text skip navigation SENATE PRESIDENT SENATORS COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS SENATE CLERK SENATE RULES HOUSE SPEAKER DELEGATES COMMITTEES VIDEO/AUDIO DISTRICT MAPS HOUSE CLERK HOUSE RULES HOUSE STAFF JOINT INTERIM COMMITTEES LEGISLATIVE ADMINISTRATOR LEGISLATIVE SERVICES DIVISION PUBLIC INFORMATION LEGISLATIVE AUTOMATED SYSTEMS DIVISION LEGISLATIVE AUDITOR'S OFFICE PERFORMANCE EVALUATION & RESEARCH DIVISION POST AUDIT DIVISION BUDGET DIVISION REGULATORY AND FISCAL AFFAIRS DIVISION CLAIMS COMMISSION CRIME VICTIMS RULE-MAKING REVIEW SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS JUDICIAL COMP. COMMISSION JOINT RULES STAFF INFO BILL STATUS BILL STATUS BILL TRACKING STATE LAW WEST VIRGINIA CODE ACTS OF THE LEGISLATURE CODE OF 1931 WV CONSTITUTION US CONSTITUTION REPORTS AGENCY REPORTS AGENCY GRANT AWARDS PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS POST AUDITS EDUCATIONAL CITIZEN’S GUIDE INTERNSHIP PROGRAM PAGE PROGRAM PUBLICATIONS PHOTO GALLERY CAPITOL HISTORY HOW A BILL BECOMES LAW CONTACT SENATE ROSTER HOUSE ROSTER PUBLIC INFO. NEWS RELEASES HELPFUL LINKS Introduced Version Senate Resolution 5 History |  Email Key: Green = existing Code. Red = new code to be enacted SENATE RESOLUTION 5(By Senator Chapman)[Introduced February 13, 2025] Designating February 14, 2025, as National Organ Donor Day at the Legislature.Whereas, The State of West Virginia recognizes February 14, 2025, as National Donor Day, a day to celebrate those who save and heal lives as organ, tissue, and cornea donors; andWhereas, The State of West Virginia honors the memory of Seilah Andrea Stanley, a vibrant two-year-old who brought immeasurable joy to her family and community with her playful spirit and loving nature. Following a tragic accident in June 2024, her parents, Logan and Angie Stanley, made the courageous decision to donate her organs, saving the lives of two children and one adult. Seilah’s selfless gift of life serves as a powerful reminder of the impact organ donation can have and ensures that her legacy will continue to inspire and bless others; andWhereas, The Center for Organ Recovery and Education (CORE) is the Organ Procurement Organization (OPO) serving most of West Virginia; andWhereas, CORE marked a sixth consecutive record-breaking year in 2024 in organ, tissue, and cornea donation; andWhereas, In West Virginia, there was a 33 percent increase in total organ, tissue, and cornea donors in 2024; andWhereas, More than 100,000 individuals in the United States, including 500 West Virginians, are currently awaiting a life-saving organ transplant; andWhereas, Every 10 minutes, a person is added to the national transplant registry waiting list. On average, 17 people in the United States die each day because the needed organ is not donated in time; andWhereas, One organ donor can save the lives of eight people and heal 75 others; andWhereas, West Virginia encourages all residents to register as an organ, tissue, and cornea donor online at donatelifewv.org, at their local West Virginia DMV offices, or on their West Virginia hunting and fishing license application; therefore, be itResolved by the Senate:That the Senate hereby designates February 14, 2025, as National Organ Donor Day at the Legislature; and, be it Further Resolved, That the Clerk is hereby directed to forward a copy of this resolution to the family of Seilah Andrea Stanley. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


